0pumps%20that%20extract%20heat%2C%20transfer%20it%20to%20water%20in%20another%20system%20of%20pipes%2C%20and%20concentrate%20it%20to%20raise%20the%20water%20temperature%20as%20high%20as%2080%20degrees%20Celsius.%20The%20pipes%20then%20carry%20that%20hot%20water%20to%20homes%20in%20the%20area%2C%20where%20the%20heat%20is%20transferred%20once%20more%20to%20the%20buildings'%20furnaces%20and%20boilers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20project%2C%20called%20the%20Neighbourhood%20Energy%20Utility%2C%20began%20in%202010%20when%20the%20city%20built%20a%20sustainability-centric%20village%20for%20the%20Winter%20Olympics.%20To%20heat%20new%20homes%20with%20minimal%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20the%20city%20turned%20to%20the%20sewage%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20was%20a%20bold%20decision%2C%20and%20one%20that%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20very%20good%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20Derek%20Pope%2C%20who%20manages%20the%20NEU%20project%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20project%20started%20out%20heating%20nine%20residential%20buildings.%20Today%20NEU%20delivers%20recycled%20sewer%20heat%20to%2044%20buildings%20including%20more%20than%206%2C000%20residential%20units%2C%20a%20university%20campus%2C%20a%20science%20museum%2C%20and%20commercial%20facilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPope%20said%20the%20heat%20pumps%20have%20300%25%20efficiency%3A%20For%20every%20unit%20of%20electricity%20that%20powers%20them%2C%20the%20utility%20gets%20three%20units%20of%20thermal%20energy.%20By%20contrast%2C%20Pope%20said%2C%20when%20the%20system%20has%20to%20top%20off%20the%20heating%20supply%20with%20natural%20gas%20in%20periods%20of%20high%20demand%2C%20that%20has%20efficiency%20below%20100%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22tall%20stacks%20with%20rectangle%20purple%20lights%20on%20top%20glow%20in%20the%20night%20beside%20a%20highway%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64766d08085acb0018fef05a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221050%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20NEU%20energy%20center%20is%20beneath%20a%20bridge.%20The%20%26quot%3Bfingernails%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20LED%20panels%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20boiler%20stacks%20%E2%80%94%20change%20color%20depending%20on%20how%20much%20energy%20is%20being%20pulled%20from%20the%20system.%3Cp%3ECity%20of%20Vancouver%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20system%20delivers%20a%20%26quot%3Bmodest%20return%20on%20the%20city's%20investment%2C%26quot%3B%20Pope%20said%2C%20because%20it's%20run%20like%20a%20public%20utility%20for%20a%20slight%20profit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202022%20report%20to%20the%20City%20Council%2C%20the%20utility%20found%20that%20for%20customers%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20recycled%20heat%20was%20in%20line%20with%20that%20of%20other%20local%20energy%20and%20heating%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENEU's%20upgrades%20have%20expanded%20its%20customer%20base%2C%20adding%20buildings%20to%20its%20network.%20Now%20the%20utility%20is%20tripling%20its%20heat-recycling%20capacity%20by%20installing%20two%20more%20heat%20pumps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20large%20heat%20pump%20covered%20in%20white%20wrapping%20hangs%20from%20an%20outdoor%20blue%20scaffolding%20over%20a%20rectangular%20hole%20in%20concrete%20ground%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64766d1b085acb0018fef06d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWorkers%20gently%20lowering%20a%20new%20heat%20pump%20into%20the%20NEU%20energy%20center.%3Cp%3ECity%20of%20Vancouver%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENEU's%20success%20indicates%20that%20sewage-heat%20recovery%20may%20be%20a%20sustainable%20and%20cost-effective%20option%20when%20building%20new%20urban%20areas%2C%20like%20an%20Olympic%20Village.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EData%20centers%20can%20heat%20homes%20too%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%20ocean%2C%20Stockholm%20is%20tapping%20into%20a%20major%20heat%20source%3A%20data%20centers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20world%20needs%20more%20and%20more%20of%20these%20warehouses%20of%20computer%20servers%20to%20process%20and%20store%20information.%20All%20that%20computing%2C%20concentrated%20in%20one%20building%2C%20gets%20hot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20seems%20very%20strange%20that%20we%20should%20let%20out%20excess%20heat%20when%20we%20can%20actually%20buy%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Johanna%20Nerell%2C%20a%20project%20manager%20at%20the%20utility%20Stockholm%20Exergi%2C%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20make%20money%20for%20the%20company%20who%20delivers%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20buys%20captured%20waste%20heat%20from%20nearby%20data%20centers%20and%20funnels%20it%20to%20homes.%20It's%20part%20of%20what%20Exergi%20calls%20an%20%26quot%3Bopen%20district%20heating%26quot%3B%20system%2C%20which%20draws%20waste%20heat%20from%20different%20businesses%20in%20the%20city%2C%20including%20a%20yeast-production%20plant%20and%20a%20supermarket%2C%20as%20well%20as%20sewage.%20Data%20centers%20contribute%20the%20lion's%20share%2C%20accounting%20for%2090%25%20of%20open%20district%20heat%2C%20Nerell%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221125%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22infographic%20shows%20pink%20lines%20flowing%20out%20of%20a%20data%20center%20underground%20and%20through%20a%20home%20with%20a%20shower%20and%20space%20heater%20an%20purple%20lines%20flowing%20back%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64a75a064cc8540019cbac17%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20chart%20showing%20how%20Stockholm%20Exergi%20funnels%20heat%20from%20data%20centers%2C%20at%20the%20bottom%2C%20to%20homes.%3Cp%3EStockholm%20Exergi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20in%20all%2C%20Nerell%20said%2C%20this%20heat-recycling%20network%20accounts%20for%201.5%25%20of%20the%20heat%20Exergi%20delivers%20throughout%20Stockholm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20likely%20we%20will%20never%20get%20much%20higher%20than%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Nerell%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20would've%20been%20different%20if%20we%20had%20industries%20surrounding%20Stockholm%20that%20produce%20a%20lot%20of%20excess%20heat.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20heavy%20industries%2C%20only%20a%20few%20types%20of%20businesses%20can%20make%20the%20up-front%20investment%20to%20install%20the%20heat%20pumps%20and%20pipes%20needed%20to%20sell%20their%20heat%2C%20she%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BThat's%20where%20data%20centers%20are%20ideal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThere's%20more%20untapped%20heat%20underground%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20urban%20heat%20island%20%E2%80%94%20the%20churn%20of%20activity%20that%20makes%20cities%20hotter%20%E2%80%94%20extends%20underground%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222220%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20uses%20a%20newspaper%20to%20cool%20himself%20while%20on%20the%20tube.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62d5f8a7f7ae65001834086b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221665%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20man%20using%20a%20newspaper%20as%20a%20fan%20on%20the%20subway%20in%20central%20London%20during%20a%20heat%20wave.%3Cp%3EYui%20Mok%2FPA%20Images%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EExcess%20heat%20can%20harm%20river%20ecosystems%20fed%20by%20groundwater%2C%20since%20fish%20and%20other%20life-forms%20there%20generally%20prefer%20cool%20water%20flowing%20from%20underground.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverheated%20groundwater%20also%20affects%20drinking-water%20quality%2C%20since%20the%20warmth%20can%20breed%20bacteria%20or%20cause%20more%20heavy%20metals%20to%20leach%20from%20the%20surrounding%20soil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20possible%20to%20cool%20the%20underground%20and%20cut%20fossil-fuel%20use%20by%20capturing%20the%20heat%20beneath%20the%20surface%2C%20researchers%20found%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Dc8855f14c0a6faa38393b17da416ceaede06ff6d6f3b91b2f610a89af384b97d%26postID%3D64765d768c8a4f7ad11eaf43%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41467-022-31624-6%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20Nature%20Communications%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20two%20birds%20with%20one%20stone%2C%26quot%3B%20Susanne%20Benz%2C%20an%20author%20of%20the%20study%20who%20researches%20subsurface%20heat%2C%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BCarbon-free%20energy%2C%20and%20at%20the%20same%20time%20we%20get%20to%20reduce%20the%20impact%20of%20climate%20change%20and%20urbanization%20on%20our%20environment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBenz%20and%20her%20colleagues%20assessed%20over%208%2C000%20locations%20where%20measurements%20of%20groundwater%20temperature%20were%20available%2C%20mostly%20in%20Europe.%20They%20found%20that%20in%20about%2025%25%20of%20those%20places%20there%20was%20enough%20heat%20underground%20to%20recycle%20for%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20percentage%20will%20surely%20increase%20as%20the%20planet's%20average%20temperature%20rises%2C%20heating%20up%20the%20underground%20even%20more.%20The%20study's%20authors%20estimated%20that%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20century%2C%2073%25%20of%20the%20locations%20could%20fulfill%20all%20their%20heating%20needs%20with%20underground%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22worker%20in%20neon%20green%20vest%20hardhat%20and%20respirator%20mask%20stands%20at%20the%20side%20of%20a%20long%20tall%20dark%20tunnel%20deep%20underground%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ac6a0d6d7e02001af8b6ea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20staff%20member%20standing%20at%20the%20underground%20Oyu%20Tolgoi%20copper%20mine%20in%20the%20Gobi%20Desert%20in%20Mongolia.%3Cp%3EB.%20Rentsendorj%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETapping%20into%20flowing%20groundwater%20would%20allow%20municipalities%20to%20access%20that%20heat.%20Regions%20without%20flowing%20groundwater%20would%20have%20to%20lay%20pipes%20underground%20and%20cycle%20fluid%20through%20them%20to%20absorb%20the%20heat%20and%20bring%20it%20to%20the%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBenz%20says%20it's%20worth%20considering%20adding%20those%20underground%20pipes%20as%20part%20of%20new%20construction%2C%20especially%20building%20new%20streets%2C%20which%20absorb%20extra%20heat.%20Subway%20tunnels%20could%20also%20be%20an%20easy%20place%20to%20start.%20In%202020%2C%20the%20Islington%20neighborhood%20of%20London%20built%20a%20system%20in%20its%20subway%20to%20funnel%20heat%20from%20those%20underground%20tunnels%20to%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20underground%20heat%20builds%20up%20the%20most%20in%20summer%2C%20when%20people%20don't%20need%20to%20heat%20their%20homes.%20But%20Benz%20said%20the%20ground%20would%20hold%20on%20to%20the%20heat%20until%20it's%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHeat%20takes%20a%20little%20bit%20to%20travel%20in%20the%20underground.%20So%20if%20you%20time%20it%20right%20and%20put%20your%20heat%20pump%20or%20your%20pipes%20at%20exactly%20the%20right%20depth%2C%20all%20the%20heat%20from%20the%20summer%20reaches%20it%20in%20winter%2C%20when%20you%20actually%20need%20the%20heating%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20ground%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnorthvolt-trying-fix-electric-vehicle-supply-chain-battery-recycling-2023-4%5C%22%3Ebattery%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20this%20case.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecycling-waste-heat-abundant-sustainable-energy-source-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689347406000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F648b77d751ea980019d69242%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww