C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Glazer%20said%20his%20primary%20clientele%20includes%20executives%20in%20finance%20who%20develop%20addictions%20to%20drugs%2C%20alcohol%2C%20and%20sex%20to%20mitigate%20the%20pressure%20of%20their%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20he%20told%20the%20Journal%20that%20one%20of%20his%20first%20patients%20was%20a%20Wall%20Street%20accountant%20whose%20life%20was%20upended%20due%20to%20their%20cocaine%20addiction%20%E2%80%94%20mental%20wellbeing%20is%20a%20problem%20that%20continues%20to%20permeate%20most%20workplaces.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20survey%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww2.deloitte.com%2Fus%2Fen%2Finsights%2Ftopics%2Ftalent%2Fworkplace-well-being-research.html%5C%22%3EDeloitte%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20a%20majority%20of%20workers%20who%20responded%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployee-wellbeing-fallen-execs-improved-deloitte-survey-mental-health-2023-6%5C%22%3Esaid%20their%20wellbeing%20had%20either%20worsened%20or%20stayed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20same%20from%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20half%20of%20the%201%2C050%20regular%20employees%20surveyed%20%26quot%3Balways%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Boften%26quot%3B%20felt%20exhausted%20(52%25)%20or%20stressed%20(49%25).%20Another%20insight%20highlighted%20that%2060%25%20of%20employees%2C%20%C2%A064%25%20of%20managers%2C%20and%2075%25%20of%20the%20C-suite%20executives%20who%20responded%20to%20the%20survey%20said%20they%20were%20%26quot%3B%20seriously%20considering%20quitting%20for%20a%20job%20that%20would%20better%20support%20their%20well-being.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinance%20jobs%2C%20which%20can%20offer%20robust%20salaries%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20first%20and%20second-year%20investment%20banking%20analysts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-responds-with-cash-bonuses-as-banker-burnout-mounts-2021-3%5C%22%3Ecan%20make%20up%20to%20%24125%2C000%20a%20year%20before%20bonus%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20interns%20can%20make%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-intern-salary-trending-upwards-2023-6%5C%22%3Eclose%20to%20%2420%2C000%20a%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20positions%20that%20are%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20hierarchy%20%E2%80%94%20also%20have%20a%20reputation%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoldman-sachs-junior-bankers-inhumane-working-conditions-survey-2021-3%5C%22%3Elong%20hours%20and%20high%20stress.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlden%20Cass%2C%20a%20psychologist%20and%20life%20coach%20that%20specializes%20in%20addiction%20and%20mental%20health%20issues%2C%20said%20he%20also%20deals%20with%20a%20similar%20clientele%20to%20Glazer%2C%20like%20private%20equity%20mangers%2C%20financial%20advisors%20at%20big%20banks%2C%20and%20hedge%20fund%20traders.%20He%20charges%20%24300%20for%20a%20session.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20completely%20honest%20with%20me%20in%20my%20office%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BBut%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20therapy%2C%20they%20are%20not%20comfortable%20divulging%20that%20with%20people%20at%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECass%20said%20his%20approach%20uses%20cognitive%20behavioral%20techniques%20to%20help%20clients%20develop%20emotional%20discipline%2C%20so%20that%20they%20can%20boost%20their%20performance%20at%20work%20as%20well.%20That%20can%20mean%20people%20are%20more%20comfortable%20being%20transparent%20about%20seeing%20a%20psychologist%2C%20he%20told%20Insider%2C%20because%20they%20can%20say%20%26quot%3Bhey%20I've%20got%20this%20performance%20coach%20that%20works%20with%20all%20the%20big%20dogs%20on%20Wall%20Street%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20him%20to%20get%20better.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20some%20may%20view%20help%20coming%20from%20a%20performance%20coach%20as%20less%20stigmatized%2C%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20Cass%20is%20assisting%20them%20with%20their%20mental%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20the%20most%20forthcoming%20clients%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20problems%20once%20you%20get%20them%20in%20the%20door%2C%26quot%3B%20Cass%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20getting%20them%20to%20feel%20safe%2C%20secure%20and%20feeling%20that%20their%20employer%20is%20not%20going%20to%20know%20about%20these%20issues.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20benefits%20of%20therapy%20are%20more%20widely%20discussed%20today%2C%20the%20costs%20can%20present%20insurmountable%20barriers%20to%20entry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.verywellmind.com%2Fcost-of-therapy-survey-5271327%5C%22%3E2022%20survey%20from%20Verywell%20Mind%3C%2Fa%3E%20highlights%20that%2080%25%20of%20its%201%2C000%20respondents%20considered%20therapy%20a%20good%20investment%20but%20nearly%20half%20(49%25)%20%26quot%3Bworry%20about%20paying%20for%20therapy%20long-term.%26quot%3B%20Additionally%2C%2031%25%20of%20those%20surveyed%20indicated%20they%20had%20stopped%20going%20to%20sessions%20entirely%20to%20save%20money%20for%20other%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20Cass%20said%20that%20his%20own%20rates%20have%20gone%20up%20over%20the%20years%2C%20after%20realizing%20his%20profile%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.psychologytoday.com%2Fus%2Ftherapists%2Falden-cass-new-york-ny%2F67907%5C%22%3EPsychology%20Today%3C%2Fa%3E%20undercuts%20his%20current%20pricing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20last%20time%20I%20updated%20that%20website%20was%20five%20years%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20Cass%20said%20of%20the%20%24200%20per%20session%20figure%20on%20the%20site.%20%26quot%3BThat%20price%20is%20so%20low.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinance-executives-paying-700-hourly-therapy-sessions-addiction-mental-health-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689343821000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F647a452792151200199f5e48%3Fforma