ing%20Wall%20Street%20%E2%80%93%20even%20as%20a%20bull%20market%20reigns%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22traders%20disagree%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F59a4638779bbfd0d288b584b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMutual%20funds%20and%20hedge%20funds%20are%20divided%20over%20bank%20stocks.%3Cp%3EReuters%20%2F%20Richard%20Drew%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20hedge%20fund%20industry%20is%20grappling%20with%20a%20protracted%20period%20of%20withdrawals%20as%20investor%20interest%20in%20the%20sector%20recedes.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFor%20twelve%20consecutive%20months%2C%20the%20sector%20has%20experienced%20net%20outflows%20%E2%80%93%20coupled%20with%20the%20worst%20May%20since%202009.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20industry's%20total%20Wall%20Street%20exposure%20has%20fallen%20to%20the%20lowest%20in%20over%2010%20years%20%E2%80%93%20despite%20US%20stocks%20enjoying%20a%20remarkable%202023%20bull%20run.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EHedge%20funds%20continue%20to%20reel%20from%20a%20prolonged%20period%20of%20withdrawals%20%E2%80%93%20this%20year%2C%20the%20industry%20had%20to%20cope%20with%20the%20worst%20outflows%20for%20the%20month%20of%20May%20since%20the%20global%20financial%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20twelve%20consecutive%20months%2C%20hedge%20funds%20experienced%20net%20withdrawals%20%E2%80%93%20and%20in%20May%2C%20the%20industry%20saw%20its%20assets%20shrink%20by%20%2418.8%20billion%20due%20to%20a%20combination%20of%20investors%20pulling%20out%20and%20performance%20losses%2C%20according%20to%20asset%20management%20data%20provider%20eVestment%2C%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Nasdaq%20group.%20This%20is%20the%20biggest%20outflow%20for%20the%20month%20of%20May%20since%202009.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20as%20annual%20net%20outflows%20began%20to%20be%20the%20norm%20for%20the%20industry%20in%202018%2C%20net%20flows%20in%20May%20were%20still%20positive%20more%20often%20than%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20Peter%20Laurelli%2C%20global%20head%20of%20research%20at%20eVestment%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20recent%20note.%20%26quot%3BThe%20net%20outflow%20in%20May%202023%2C%20while%20not%20generally%20large%2C%20was%20the%20largest%20net%20outflow%20value%20we've%20seen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20provider%20attributes%20the%20trend%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20new%20investor%20interest%20in%20the%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLooking%20more%20closely%20at%20the%20breakdown%20of%20the%20data%20shows%20that%20it%20wasn't%20so%20much%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20was%20being%20removed%2C%20or%20that%20redemptions%20were%20widespread%2C%20rather%20there%20was%20a%20relatively%20normal%20level%20of%20redemptions%20along%20with%20the%20lowest%20level%20of%20meaningful%20product%20level%20net%20inflows%2C%26quot%3B%20Laurelli%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAttempting%20to%20be%20blunt%E2%80%A6there%20was%20little%20evidence%20of%20meaningful%20new%20interest%20in%20hedge%20funds%20in%20May.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHedge%20funds%20with%20equity-focused%20strategies%20have%20continued%20to%20face%20redemption%20pressures%2C%20according%20to%20Laurelli.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20sentiment%20appears%20to%20be%20shifting%20across%20some%20segments%20of%20the%20industry%2C%20it%20has%20stayed%20the%20same%20within%20equity-focused%20strategies.%20Long%2Fshort%20equity%20funds%20continue%20to%20endure%20a%20not%20impossible%2C%20but%20clearly%20difficult%20capital%20raising%2Fmaintaining%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F598cf154-86e6-408f-ad7d-c3a373d58141%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EResearch%20by%20the%20Financial%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20shown%20that%20hedge%20funds'%20total%20Wall%20Street%20exposure%20is%20at%20its%20lowest%20level%20in%20more%20than%20a%20decade.%20Despite%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500's%20remarkable%20bull%20run%20in%202023%20%E2%80%93%20rising%2018%25%20year-to-date%20%E2%80%93%20fund%20managers%20are%20ignoring%20companies%20they%20consider%20overvalued%20and%20seeking%20returns%20in%20cheaper%20European%20markets%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20justify%20the%20multiples%20of%20many%20of%20these%20%5BUS%5D%20tech%20businesses%2C%26quot%3B%20Alison%20Savas%2C%20investment%20director%20at%20Australia-based%20Antipodes%20Partners%2C%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20the%20FT.%20Her%20firm%20has%20allocated%2030%25%20of%20its%20%2410%20billion%20assets%20under%20management%20to%20Europe%20%E2%80%93%20shunning%20the%20pricier%20US%20market.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECommenting%20upon%20hefty%20tech-stock%20valuations%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20agree%20Nvidia%20is%20a%20great%20business%2C%20but%20as%20a%20value%20investor%20we%20can't%20make%20that%20multiple%20work.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stock%20market%20continues%20to%20defy%20doomsayers%2C%20however%20%E2%80%93%20with%20the%20Nasdaq%20Composite%20up%20around%2035%25%20year-to-date.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhedge-funds-reeling-from-worst-outflows-since-great-recession-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689343720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64218d9d0237f90018530f7f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Ffunds%2Fhedge-funds-reeling-from-worst-outflows-since-great-recession-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20hedge%20fund%20industry%20has%20experienced%20some%20of%20its%20biggest%20outflows%20since%202009%20as%20investor%20interest%20in%20the%20sector%20recedes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jwilkins%40insider.com%20(Joseph%20Wilkins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%