re.in%2Ffilm%2Fkashmir-files-propaganda-badly-made%5C%22%3Epropaganda%20vehicle%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fkashmir-files-propaganda-badly-made%5C%22%3EThe%20Kashmir%20Files%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20well%20remember%20how%20he%20defended%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20brazen%20bending%20of%20facts%2C%20showing%20every%20Muslim%20in%20Kashmir%20as%20a%20villain%2C%20and%20claimed%20that%20his%20being%20a%20Kashmiri%20stood%20testimony%20to%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98authenticity%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20far%20as%20the%20Tagore%20film%20goes%2C%20it%20is%20unclear%20yet%20what%20this%20film%20is%20about%20and%20what%20is%20the%20context%20of%20Kher%20playing%20the%20poet.%20But%20given%20the%20timing%20of%20the%20film%2C%20some%20amount%20of%20dread%20is%20natural%20and%20understandable.%20The%20rightwing%20ecosystem%20is%20now%20relishing%2C%20with%20frightening%20regularity%2C%20the%20misuse%20of%20popular%20cinema%20as%20brazen%20propaganda.%20Kher%E2%80%99s%20inclusion%20provokes%20the%20possibility%20that%20this%20could%20be%20another%20despicable%20sample%20of%20cinema%20that%20will%20undertake%20one%20more%20attempt%20to%20retrofit%20history%20and%20brainwash%20the%20gullible%20public%20into%20buying%20a%20work%20of%20fiction%20as%20some%20kind%20of%20truth%20so%20far%20hidden%20from%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20much%20is%20understandable.%20But%20should%20this%20mean%20he%20is%20proscribed%20from%20playing%20Tagore%3F%20Kher%20is%20a%20veteran%20thespian%20and%20even%20those%20who%20dislike%20him%20wholeheartedly%20for%20what%20he%20has%20done%20to%20the%20liberal%20ethos%20of%20Hindi%20popular%20cinema%2C%20cannot%20look%20away%20from%20some%20of%20his%20tall%20performances%3A%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESaransh%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(1984)%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKarma%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(1986)%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPestonjee%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(1987)%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Eand%20the%20more%20recent%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKhosla%20ka%20Ghosla%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(2006)%20for%20example.%20There%20is%20no%20reason%20to%20believe%2C%20from%20a%20performative%20standpoint%2C%20that%20Kher%20is%20%E2%80%98unsuitable%E2%80%99%20to%20play%20Tagore.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20the%20much%20more%20important%20question%20is%2C%20should%20an%20actor%E2%80%99s%20ideology%20and%20politics%20be%20a%20defining%20factor%20in%20acting%20out%20a%20role%2C%20particularly%20in%20a%20scenario%20of%20a%20biopic%3F%20Or%20is%20there%20something%20more%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIs%20the%20disapproval%20something%20to%20do%20with%20Kher%20not%20being%20a%20Bengali%20and%20not%20knowing%20the%20language%3F%20This%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20travesty%20and%20came%20up%20among%20many%20Bengalis%20who%20tut-tutted%20about%20the%20Mumbai%20actor%20playing%20the%20role.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20would%20be%20somewhat%20self-defeating.%20Cinema%E2%80%99s%20unique%20appeal%20has%20been%20historically%20to%20neutralise%20an%20actor%E2%80%99s%20native%20language%20to%20enable%20him%20or%20her%20to%20aim%20for%20performative%20participation.%20Otherwise%2C%20Burt%20Lancaster%20would%20not%20have%20played%20a%20Sicilian%20aristocrat%20in%20Visconti%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Leopard%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(1963)%2C%20Alain%20Delon%20would%20not%20be%20in%20Antonioni%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EL%E2%80%99Eclisse%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(1962)%20or%20Joaquin%20Phoenix%20could%20not%20act%20as%20Napoleon%20in%20the%20forthcoming%20Ridley%20Scott%20epic.%20Closer%20home%2C%20there%20are%20other%20examples%2C%20where%20the%20actors%20do%20not%20share%20any%20identifiable%20resemblance%2C%20except%20maybe%20a%20passing%20physical%20one%2C%20with%20the%20roles%20they%20would%20be%20enacting.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20two%20best%20actors%20to%20have%20played%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20among%20numerous%20others%20%E2%80%93%20Ben%20Kingsley%20on%20screen%20and%20Naseeruddin%20Shah%20on%20stage%20%E2%80%93%20are%20not%20particularly%20in%20the%20mould%20of%20being%20a%20%E2%80%98Gandhian%E2%80%99.%20The%20same%20goes%20for%20the%20numerous%20actors%20who%20have%20played%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%2C%20Roshan%20Seth%20included.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EMammootty%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20who%20played%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20in%20Jabbar%20Patel%E2%80%99s%20eponymous%20biopic%2C%20is%20neither%20a%20Maharashtrian%20nor%20from%20any%20of%20the%20caste%20groups%20championed%20by%20Ambedkar.%20So%20far%20there%20has%20been%20no%20major%20disapproval%20from%20Gujaratis%2C%20Kashmiris%20or%20Ambedkarites%20respectively.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20three%20are%20the%20most%20recognisable%20political%20figures%20in%20all%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20history.%20The%20nature%20of%20their%20iconicity%20could%20have%20provoked%20deep%20dismay%20about%20the%20actors%E2%80%99%20own%20beliefs%20or%20linguistic%20background.%20But%20that%20did%20not%20happen.%20One%20would%20like%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20functional%20need%20to%20have%20a%20performer%20of%20some%20talent%20and%20screen%20presence%20were%20the%20decisive%20factors%20here%2C%20not%20their%20person.%20Whether%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EKher%20is%20as%20talented%20as%20those%20named%20earlier%20is%20not%20the%20question%20here%3B%20the%20criticism%20has%20been%20not%20being%20either%20a%20liberal%20or%20a%20bonafide%20Bengali%20is%20what%20is%20troublesome.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F10%2FAnupam-Kher_PTI-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Anupam%20Kher.%20Credit%3A%20PTI%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22797%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-187078%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22483%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAnupam%20Kher.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMoreover%2C%20one%20may%20note%20that%20several%20actors%20have%20played%20Tagore%20in%20Bengali%20cinema%2C%20and%20almost%20all%20those%20films%20are%20rather%20forgettable.%20The%20most%20recent%20of%20them%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThinking%20of%20Him%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(2022)%2C%20an%20Indo-Argentinian%20film%20based%20on%20Tagore%E2%80%99s%20late-life%20friendship%20with%20the%20Argentine%20writer%20Victoria%20Ocampo.%20No%20one%20saw%20the%20film%2C%20let%20alone%20create%20a%20fuss%20about%20Victor%20Banerjee%20playing%20Tagore%2C%20he%20being%20one%20of%20the%20earliest%20actors%20in%20Bengal%20to%20have%20fought%20an%20election%20on%20a%20BJP%20ticket.%20Shall%20we%20then%20say%20that%20Bannerjee%20and%20his%20politics%20are%20acceptable%20because%20he%20is%20a%20Bengali%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EParambrata%20Chatterjee%E2%80%99s%20young%20Tagore%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKadambini%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(2015)%20was%20somewhat%20watchable%2C%20something%20that%20cannot%20be%20said%20about%20Sanjoy%20Nag%E2%80%99s%20version%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20Rituparno%20Ghosh%E2%80%99s%20quasi-documentary%20on%20Tagore%20life-%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EJibonsmriti%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(2013).%20There%20are%20other%20examples%20of%20much%20lower%20sensibility%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Etalent.%20Why%20no%20disapproval%20of%20them%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20more%20sensible%20response%20would%20be%20to%20ignore%20the%20criticism%20or%20just%20to%20pass%20them%20with%20a%20mix%20of%20laughter%20and%20a%20sigh%2C%20like%20one%20does%20when%20passing%20by%20those%20god-awful%20mofussil%20statues.%20There%20one%20is%20likely%20to%20bemoan%20the%20lack%20of%20street%20aesthetic%20and%20the%20perversion%20of%20public%20art%2C%20not%20really%20if%20that%20statue%20is%20suitable%20for%20the%20stature%20of%20Tagore.%20Evidently%2C%20they%20aren%E2%80%99t.%20The%20yardstick%20should%20be%20the%20same%20for%20another%20film%20on%20Tagore%2C%20whether%20it%20has%20Anupam%20Kher%20or%20Shah%20Rukh%20Khan%20playing%20the%20Nobel-winning%20literary%20titan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFinally%2C%20there%20is%20also%20%E2%80%98that%E2%80%99%20question%20of%20letting%20Tagore%20out%20of%20the%20grasp%20of%20claustrophobic%20Bengali%20stranglehold%2C%20something%20that%20Ramchandra%20Guha%20has%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia%2Fthe-man-who-saw-india%2Fstory-iG4k3Gkk8dtkBRKY4jtdAO.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewritten%20about%20time%20and%20again%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20One%20of%20the%20most%20fractious%20issues%20in%20the%20dogged%20and%20continuing%20ownership%20of%20Tagore%20by%20Bengalis%20is%20to%20keep%20him%20both%20close%20to%20the%20chest%20while%20at%20the%20same%20time%20desiring%20his%20global%20approbation.%20Both%20cannot%20happen.%20Bengalis%20must%20learn%20to%20let%20go%20of%20Tagore%20simply%20being%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eone%20of%20them%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20accept%20him%20as%20a%20man%20of%20the%20world%2C%20a%20cosmopolitan%20polymath%2C%20which%20he%20was.%20To%20do%20so%2C%20Bengalis%20must%20let%20a%20thousand%20Tagores%20bloom%20%E2%80%93%20good%2C%20bad%20and%20ugly.%20Like%20Shakespeare.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20one%20must%20hope%20is%20that%20Kher%2C%20while%20playing%20Tagore%2C%20gets%20to%20learn%20the%20values%20of%20empathy%2C%20universality%20and%20humanism%20that%20Tagore%20propounded%2C%20most%20famously%20in%20his%20remarkable%20lectures%20on%20nationalism%20and%20fascism.%20The%20petrified%20and%20rather%20pathetic%20mofussil%20statues%20would%20be%20hard%20to%20put%20life%20into%2C%20but%20Kher%2C%20with%20his%20narrow-minded%20politics%2C%20may%20want%20to%20make%20a%20course%20correction%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ereturn%20to%20life%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20playing%20Tagore.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3ELet%20us%20hope%20that%20by%20enacting%20the%20great%20man%2C%20a%20bit%20of%20Tagore%20rubs%20off%20on%20Kher.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fsayandeb-chowdhury%5C%22%3ESayandeb%20Chowdhury%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20an%20academic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689336014000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F09%2F18115839%2FPortrait_of_Rabindranath_Tagore_photographed_during_Bengali_Wikipedia_10th_Anniversary_Celebration_Jadavpur_University_Campus5887-copy.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fanupam-kher-to-play-tagore-bengalis-not-amused%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Perhaps%20the%20humanist%20poet%E2%80%99s%20liberal%20ideas%20will%20rub%20off%20on%20the%20actor%2C%20who%20has%20made%20no%20secret%20of%20his%20right%20wing%20political%20ideology.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fanupam-kher-to-play-tagore-bengalis-not-amused%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Australian%20Guild%20Says%20Fully%20Local%20Productions%20Are%20Unaffected%20by%20SAG-AFTRA%20Strike%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689335991000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2FLa-Brea-NBC.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235670384%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Screen%20Producers%20Australia%2C%20an%20Australian%20guild%2C%20moved%20quickly%20on%20Friday%20to%20explain%20that%20wholly%20local%20film%20and%20TV%20productions