20workers%20are%20actively%20disengaged%20in%20the%20job%20and%20%26quot%3Bthey%20are%20not%20afraid%20to%20show%20it%26quot%3B%2C%20as%20per%20a%20report%20in%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffortune.com%2F2023%2F06%2F27%2Ffrustrated-employees-loud-quiet-quitting-resignation-trend-worse-business-leaders-gallup%2F%5C%22%3E%20%3Cem%3EFortune%20Magazine%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20cited%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gallup.com%2Fworkplace%2F349484%2Fstate-of-the-global-workplace.aspx%5C%22%3EState%20of%20the%20Global%20Workplace%202023%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Gallup.%20The%20report%20assessed%20more%20than%201.2%20lakh%20employees%20across%20the%20globe%20and%20concluded%20that%20roughly%2018%20per%20cent%20or%20almost%20one%20in%20five%20of%20all%20global%20employees%20are%20actively%20disengaged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGallup%20explained%20in%20their%20report%2C%20%26quot%3BThese%20employees%20take%20actions%20that%20directly%20harm%20the%20organisation%2C%20undercutting%20its%20goals%20and%20opposing%20its%20leaders.%26quot%3B%20An%20example%20of%20the%20same%20can%20include%20an%20employee%20posting%20negative%20things%20about%20their%20employer%20before%20sending%20out%20a%20resignation%20mail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Fortune%2C%20loud%20quitters%20seem%20more%20dangerous%20as%20they%20not%20only%20express%20negative%20emotions%20about%20their%20boss%20but%20also%20drag%20the%20organisation%20down%20before%20they%20leave.%20%26quot%3BThey%20aren't%20just%20unhappy%20at%20work.%20They%20are%20resentful%20that%20their%20needs%20aren't%20being%20met%20and%20are%20acting%20out%20their%20unhappiness.%20Every%20day%2C%20these%20workers%20potentially%20undermine%20what%20their%20engaged%20coworkers%20accomplish%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Gallup%20report%20noted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDiscussing%20the%20reason%20behind%20the%20same%2C%20the%20report%20noted%20that%20at%20some%20point%20during%20the%20course%20of%20employment%2C%20the%20employee%20feels%20that%20they%20are%20not%20suitable%20for%20their%20profile%20or%20are%20%26quot%3Bunengaged%20by%20their%20manager%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BAt%20some%20point%20along%20the%20way%2C%20the%20trust%20between%20employee%20and%20employer%20was%20severely%20broken.%20Or%20the%20employee%20has%20been%20woefully%20mismatched%20to%20a%20role%2C%20causing%20constant%20crises%2C%26quot%3B%20Gallup%20added.%20However%2C%20they%20said%20that%20the%20management%20is%20mostly%20at%20fault%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20manager%20is%20responsible%20for%2070%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20team's%20involvement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGallup%20further%20commented%2C%20%26quot%3BPoor%20management%20leads%20to%20lost%20customers%20and%20lost%20profits%2C%20but%20it%20also%20leads%20to%20miserable%20lives.%20It%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Bhaving%20a%20job%20you%20hate%20is%20worse%20than%20being%20unemployed%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689333360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fgejmvpo_quit_625x300_14_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-what-is-loud-quitting-the-new-workplace-trend-4207222%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20the%20name%20suggests%2C%20%26quot%3Bloud%20quitting%26quot%3B%2C%20which%20is%20completely%20opposite%20to%20%26quot%3Bquiet%20quitting%26quot%3B%2C%20refers%20to%20the%20trend%20where%20workers%20are%20actively%20disengaged%20in%20the%20job%20and%20%26quot%3Bthey%20are%20not%20afraid%20to%20show%20it%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-what-is-loud-quitting-the-new-workplace-trend-4207222%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-what-is-loud-quitting-the-new-workplace-trend-4207222%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-what-is-loud-quitting-the-new-wor