tv256d6f9%5C%22%3E%20March%20for%20Equality%20and%20Against%20Racism%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20which%20attracted%20at%20least%20100%2C000%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202005%2C%20there%20was%20another%20incident%20with%20many%20parallels%20to%20Nahel%E2%80%99s%20murder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20teenagers%2C%20aged%20between%2015%20and%2017%2C%20were%20returning%20home%20one%20afternoon%20after%20playing%20football%20with%20their%20friends%20when%20they%20were%20suddenly%20followed%20by%20the%20police.%20Although%20they%20had%20done%20nothing%20wrong%20(and%20this%20was%20later%20confirmed%20by%20an%20investigation)%2C%20the%20terrified%20youngsters%20hid%20in%20an%20electrical%20transformer%20to%20escape%20the%20police.%20Two%20of%20them%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Ffeatures%2F2017%2F10%2F27%2Fwhen-bouana-traores-death-led-to-frances-2005-riots%5C%22%3EZyed%20Benna%20and%20Bouna%20Traor%C3%A9%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20died%20of%20electrocution.%20The%20third%2C%20Muhittin%20Altun%2C%20suffered%20terrible%20burns%20and%20permanent%20injuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20media%2C%20however%2C%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20justify%20their%20brutal%20murder%2C%20scrutinised%20the%20victims%E2%80%99%20backgrounds%20and%20criminalised%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENicolas%20Sarkozy%2C%20who%20was%20then%20Minister%20of%20the%20Interior%2C%20Internal%20Security%20and%20Local%20Freedoms%2C%20blamed%20the%20youngsters%20for%20what%20had%20happened%20to%20them%20with%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vie-publique.fr%2Fdiscours%2F150070-interview-de-m-nicolas-sarkozy-ministre-de-linterieur-et-de-lamenage%5C%22%3Ebizarre%20remark%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20have%20nothing%20to%20hide%2C%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20run%20when%20you%20see%20the%20police.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ffrances-history-with-racist-police-violence%5C%22%3EFrance%E2%80%99s%20History%20With%20Racist%20Police%20Violence%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPolice%20violence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20cases%20of%20police%20violence%20is%20steadily%20increasing%20every%20year%20in%20France.%20According%20to%20Defender%20of%20Rights%2C%20an%20independent%20constitutional%20authority%2C%20in%20France%2C%20young%20men%20of%20black%20or%20North%20African%20origin%20are%2020%20times%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20subjected%20to%20identity%20checks%20by%20the%20police%20than%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcommentisfree%2F2023%2Fjun%2F30%2Ffrance-racist-police-violence-riots-nahel%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EGuardian%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%201999%2C%20France%20was%20convicted%20of%20torture%20by%20the%20European%20Court%20of%20Human%20Rights%20after%20a%20teenager%20of%20North%20African%20origin%20was%20sexually%20abused%20by%20police.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202012%2C%20Human%20Rights%20Watch%20had%20reported%20that%20the%20ID%20check%20system%20had%20been%20abused%20by%20the%20French%20police%2C%20and%20in%202016%2C%20the%20French%20courts%20had%20condemned%20the%20state%20for%20%E2%80%9Cgross%20negligence%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202022%2C%20the%20UN%20Committee%20on%20the%20Elimination%20of%20Racial%20Discrimination%20condemned%20both%20politicians%E2%80%99%20racist%20rhetoric%20and%20police%20ID%20checks%20that%20%E2%80%9Cdisproportionately%20target%20specific%20minorities%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-66066438%5C%22%3E2017%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20it%20easier%20for%20police%20to%20use%20firearms.%20Police%20officers%20can%20now%20fire%20in%20%E2%80%98self%20defence%E2%80%99%20without%20even%20having%20to%20justify%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20researcher%20Sebastian%20Roch%C3%A9%2C%20since%20the%20change%20in%20the%20law%2C%20the%20number%20of%20fatal%20shootings%20of%20moving%20vehicles%20has%20increased%20fivefold.%20Last%20year%2C%2013%20people%20were%20shot%20dead%20in%20their%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20riots%2C%20the%20United%20Nations%20said%20that%20France%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.africanews.com%2F2023%2F06%2F30%2Ffrance-must-address-deep-police-racism-un%2F%2F%5C%22%3Emust%20address%3C%2Fa%3E%20deep%20problems%20of%20racial%20discrimination%20in%20its%20police%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENahel%E2%80%99s%20death%20during%20a%20traffic%20stop%20has%20revived%20long-standing%20complaints%20about%20policing%20and%20racial%20profiling%20in%20France%E2%80%99s%20low%20income%20and%20multi-ethnic%20suburbs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20launch%20of%20an%20investigation%20into%20the%20alleged%20premeditated%20murder%20is%20an%20opportunity%20to%20seriously%20address%20the%20deep-seated%20problems%20of%20racism%20and%20discrimination%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ravina%20Shamdasani%2C%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20UN%20Human%20Rights%20Office%2C%20said%20at%20a%20press%20conference%20in%20Geneva.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ffrench-riots-rage-resolution%5C%22%3EFrench%20Riots%20Follow%20Decades-Old%20Pattern%20of%20Rage%2C%20With%20No%20Resolution%20In%20Sight%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20the%20French%20foreign%20ministry%20rejected%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20claim%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20accusation%20of%20racism%20or%20systematic%20discrimination%20in%20France%E2%80%99s%20police%20force%20is%20completely%20unfounded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20media%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20French%20press%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3ELiberation%3C%2Fem%3E%20newspaper%20wrote%3A%20%E2%80%9CNahel%E2%80%99s%20death%20underlines%20the%20profound%20failures%20of%20an%20untouchable%20institution%3A%20excessive%20security%20measures%2C%20reduced%20training%20times%2C%20easier%20handling%20of%20weapons%E2%80%A6To%20what%20end%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELe%20Figaro%3C%2Fem%3E%20wrote%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20death%20of%20the%20young%20Nahel%20has%20triggered%20a%20wave%20of%20urban%20violence%20that%20the%20police%20are%20struggling%20to%20contain%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20important%20goal%20for%20good%20journalism%20is%20to%20give%20a%20voice%20to%20all%20parties%20involved.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%20there%20is%20the%20defence%20of%20the%20police%20officer%20and%20on%20the%20other%20the%20family%20of%20the%20young%20man%20who%20was%20murdered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20the%20viewers%20of%20the%20footage%20see%20is%20that%20this%20was%20an%20illegitimate%20act%20%E2%80%93%20despite%20the%20excuse%20of%20%E2%80%98self%20defence%E2%80%99.%20They%20see%20that%20the%20police%20officer%20was%20on%20the%20side%20of%20the%20car%2C%20that%20the%20car%20stopped%20and%20when%20it%20started%20moving%20again%2C%20he%20shot%20Nahel%20in%20the%20chest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20media%20should%20not%20report%20that%20the%20police%20shot%20someone%20in%20the%20chest%20because%20they%20felt%20threatened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20police%20violence%2C%20the%20murder%20of%20Nahel%20has%20also%20opened%20the%20debate%20on%20the%20complex%20working%20conditions%20that%20police%20officers%20face%20every%20day.%20The%20difficulties%20of%20being%20a%20police%20officer%20and%20maintaining%20law%20and%20order%20are%20also%20a%20theme%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20constantly%20addressed%20in%20the%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20young%20man%E2%80%99s%20family%20and%20all%20those%20affected%20by%20his%20death%20must%20also%20be%20heard.%20It%20is%20not%20right%20to%20ignore%20the%20emotional%20dimension%20of%20the%20story.%20Journalists%20have%20a%20duty%20to%20report%20this%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERacist%20messages%20and%20threats%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20Nahel%20was%20killed%2C%20journalists%20and%20activists%20who%20have%20focused%20on%20the%20truth%20of%20the%20matter%20have%20been%20subjected%20to%20violent%20harassment%2C%20including%20death%20threats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENewspaper%20editorial%20offices%20and%20social%20networks%20regularly%20receive%20hateful%2C%20Islamophobic%20and%20racist%20messages%20based%20on%20the%20broad%20theme%20of%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20must%20destroy%20these%20vermin%20Arabs%20and%20shoot%20them%20with%20live%20bullets%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20has%20been%20an%20explosion%20in%20the%20number%20of%20racist%20messages%20and%20threats%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20freelance%20journalist%20and%20activist%20Sihame%20Assbague.%20%E2%80%9CNahel%E2%80%99s%20family%20is%20not%20the%20only%20one%20receiving%20hate%20messages%20in%20this%20tense%20environment.%20Journalists%20and%20activists%20following%20the%20case%20or%20simply%20expressing%20their%20views%20on%20the%20issue%20have%20also%20been%20subjected%20to%20a%20wave%20of%20insults%20and%20threats%20on%20their%20social%20networks%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EViolent%20sexist%2C%20racist%20and%20Islamophobic%20comments%20are%20sent%20via%20direct%20messages%20as%20well.%20The%20invariable%20content%20of%20these%20direct%20messages%20is%20something%20like%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20kill%20you%20and%20burn%20down%20your%20mosques%2C%20you%20will%20see%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Responsibility%20lies%20with%20the%20parents%2C%20not%20the%20state%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20claimed%20that%20young%20people%20rioting%20in%20the%20streets%20were%20losing%20touch%20with%20reality%20by%20imitating%20violent%20scenes%20from%20video%20games%20on%20Snapchat%2C%20TikTok%20and%20other%20media.%20The%20head%20of%20state%20said%20about%20a%20third%20of%20those%20arrested%20in%20the%20three%20nights%20of%20rioting%20were%20only