0Research%20Organisation%20(ISRO)%E2%80%99s%20Chandrayaan-3%20mission%20was%20placed%20into%20orbit%20successfully%20on%20Friday%2C%20July%2014%20after%20blasting%20off%20from%20Sriharikota%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20at%202%3A35%20pm%20in%20the%20Launch%20Vehicle%20Mark-3%20(LVM3).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20propulsion%20module%2C%20which%20is%20designed%20to%20behave%20like%20a%20communications%20relay%20satellite%2C%C2%A0separated%20from%20the%20rocket%20at%202%3A51%20pm.%20It%20will%20take%20the%20lander%20and%20the%20rover%20to%20the%20moon.%20The%20mission%E2%80%99s%20primary%20goal%20is%20to%20demonstrate%20the%20ability%20to%20soft-land%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface%20and%20operate%20a%20robotic%20rover.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20the%20rover%2C%20Chandrayaan-3%20also%20has%20scientific%20payload%20like%20the%20Spectro-polarimetry%20of%20Habitable%20Planet%20Earth%20(SHAPE)%2C%20which%20will%20study%20the%20spectral%20and%20polarimetric%20measurements%20of%20Earth%20from%20the%20lunar%20orbit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mission%E2%80%99s%20path%20will%20consist%20of%20three%20stages%3A%20Earth%20orbit%20manoeuvres%2C%20trans-lunar%20injection%2C%20and%20lunar%20orbit%20manoeuvres.%20In%20the%20first%20stage%2C%20it%20will%20orbit%20the%20earth%20five%20times%2C%20increasing%20the%20distance%20it%20swings%20away%20each%20time.%20After%20the%C2%A0fifth%20manoeuvre%2C%20it%20will%20begin%20its%20journey%20towards%20the%20moon.%20This%20phase%20is%20the%20Trans%20Lunar%20Injection%20phase.%20It%20will%20then%20orbit%20the%20moon%20four%20times%2C%C2%A0coming%20closer%20each%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20reaching%20a%20circular%20orbit%20of%20100%20km%20x%20100%20km%2C%20the%20lander%20will%20separate%20from%20the%20propulsion%20module%20and%20move%20to%20a%20closer%20orbit%20of%2030%20km.%20The%20lander%20will%20then%20commence%20the%20soft-landing%20procedure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EISRO%20chief%20S.%20Somanath%2C%20science%20minister%20Jitendra%20Singh%20and%20former%20ISRO%20chief%20K.%20Sivan%20were%20among%20those%20who%20watched%20the%20takeoff%20at%20the%20Satish%20Dhawan%20Space%20Centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mission%20comes%20four%20years%20after%20the%20earlier%20Chandrayaan-2%20attempt%20to%20land%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fspace%2Fchandrayaan-2-vikram-lander-pragyan-rover-moon-base%5C%22%3EVikram%20rover%3C%2Fa%3E%20ended%20in%20failure.%20The%20rover%20crashed%20as%20it%20attempted%20a%20soft%20landing%20on%20the%20moon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20the%20United%20States%2C%20China%20and%20the%20former%20Soviet%20Union%20have%20completed%20successful%20lunar%20landings.%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20a%20Japanese%20start-up%20attempted%20to%20get%20a%20lander%20to%20the%20moon%2C%20but%20the%20object%20crashed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chandrayaan-3%20was%20built%20with%20a%20budget%20of%20around%20Rs%20600%C2%A0crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20launch%20is%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20first%20major%20mission%20since%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20announced%20policies%20to%20promote%20investment%20in%20private%20space%20launches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20plans%20for%20its%20companies%20to%20increase%20their%20share%20of%20the%20launch%20market%20fivefold%2C%20up%20from%202%25%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20sent%20its%20first%20probe%20to%20orbit%20the%20moon%20in%202008.%20In%202014%2C%20it%20became%20the%20first%20Asian%20country%20to%20put%20a%20satellite%20into%20orbit%20around%20Mars.%20Three%20years%20later%2C%20its%20space%20agency%20launched%20104%20satellites%20in%20a%20single%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ISRO%E2%80%99s%20three-day%20manned%20mission%20into%20the%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20orbit%2C%20called%20the%20Gaganyaan%20mission%2C%20is%20scheduled%20for%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689327433000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F14143729%2FScreenshot-2023-07-14-at-2.35.4